This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with the task of automatic melody harmonization. It also involves the use of machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different models, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the use of a standardized training/test split and the reporting of objective metrics suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
